'''Hemoptysis''' is the '''coughing up of blood''' or blood-stained [[sputum|mucus]] from the [[bronchi]], [[larynx]], [[vertebrate trachea|trachea]], or [[lung]]s. This can occur with [[lung cancer]], infections such as [[tuberculosis]], [[bronchitis]], or [[pneumonia]], and certain cardiovascular conditions. Hemoptysis is considered massive at {{convert|300|mL|floz|abbr=on}}.  In such cases, there are always severe injuries. The primary danger comes from choking, rather than blood loss.<ref name="Pocket medicine">{{cite book|last1=Sabatine|first1=[edited by] Marc S.|title=Pocket medicine|date=2014|publisher=Aspen Publishers, Inc|location=[S.l.]|isbn=1451193785|edition=Fifth edition.}}</ref>

